#slide([Problem Statement], [
  *What is plant fluff?*
  - Lightweight fibers from plants (poplar, dandelion)
  - Carrier of pollen and fine particles
  - Active during spring and summer
], [
  *Why it matters*
  - Rising number of allergy sufferers worldwide
  - Fluff is a major seasonal allergen
  - Significant impact on quality of life
], color1: c1, color2: c2)

#slide([Mechanism of Allergic Reaction], [
  *How does fluff trigger allergies?*
  - Inhalation of microscopic pollen particles
  - Immune system recognizes them as threats
  - Histamine release causes inflammation
  - Symptoms: sneezing, itching, swelling
], [
  *Allergy vs. Irritation*
  - True allergy: immune response
  - Irritation: mechanical impact
  - Diagnosis: skin tests, blood analysis
  - Important to distinguish for proper treatment
], color1: c1, color2: c2)

#slide([Types of Allergens], [
  *Plant-based*
  - Tree pollen (birch, poplar)
  - Grass pollen (ragweed, mugwort)
  - Mold spores
], [
  *Animal and household*
  - Pet dander and fur
  - Dust mites
  - Cockroaches and other insects
], color1: c1, color2: c2)

#slide([Statistics], [
  *Key figures*
  - Up to 40% of population affected
  - Annual growth of 5-10%
  - Children more susceptible than adults
], [
  *Seasonality and geography*
  - Peak season: April through August
  - Mountain regions: lower fluff levels
  - Industrial zones: higher risk
], color1: c1, color2: c2)

#slide([Prevention and Treatment], [
  *Prevention*
  - Wear masks during pollen season
  - Keep windows closed, use filtered AC
  - Rinse nose with saline solution
  - Clean home with damp methods
], [
  *Treatment*
  - Antihistamine medications
  - Nasal sprays
  - Allergen-specific immunotherapy
  - Consult an allergist
], color1: c1, color2: c2)

#slide([Conclusion], [
  *Key findings*
  - Fluff is a significant allergen
  - Early diagnosis is important
  - Prevention reduces symptoms
], [
  *Recommendations*
  - See a specialist
  - Follow precautionary measures
  - Monitor pollen forecasts
], color1: c1, color2: c2, is-last: true)
